# CODEOWNERS — automatic-review requirements per path.
#
# GitHub semantics: when a PR touches a path matching one of these globs, the
# listed owner(s) are auto-requested as reviewers. With branch protection
# "Require review from Code Owners" enabled, the PR cannot merge without
# explicit owner approval. Catches accidental skill-spec deletions (the
# pattern that caused the Step 7.4 + 7.5 regression in May 2026 via PR #1110,
# where ~330 lines of mainToProd.md were silently wiped by a wholesale
# `git checkout <stale-ref> -- .claude/` "drift catch-up").

# Skill specs — the orchestration scripts Claude reads at command invocation.
# Silent edits here change agent behavior in non-obvious ways.
.claude/commands/*.md   @alcmd15492

# PreToolUse / Stop / SessionStart hooks — enforce gates that protect main and
# production. A bad edit here can silently disable a gate.
.claude/hooks/*.sh      @alcmd15492

# Permission + MCP configuration — drift here changes what the agent can do.
.claude/settings.json   @alcmd15492
.mcp.json               @alcmd15492

# CI workflow + the section-presence lint that enforces this file.
.github/workflows/ci.yml             @alcmd15492
.github/CODEOWNERS                   @alcmd15492
scripts/check-skill-sections.sh      @alcmd15492
